---
/**
 * transactions-isolation-fundamentals · Figure 3 — Level 2, the five named
 * anomalies (+ dirty write P0 forbidden everywhere).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/transactions-isolation-fundamentals.html (figure +
 * svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro component, NOT
 * inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG
 * that uses kebab-case attrs. No arrowhead markers are referenced here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 620 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Five named anomalies, each a bad interleaving of two transactions over shared data"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="310"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">FIVE WAYS CONCURRENCY CORRUPTS DATA</text
            >
            <g>
                <rect x="12" y="36" width="190" height="58" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect>
                <text x="22" y="54" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a2218"
                    >Dirty read (P1)</text
                >
                <text x="22" y="70" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">read another txn's</text>
                <text x="22" y="82" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >uncommitted write → it aborts</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="214" y="36" width="190" height="58" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect>
                <text x="224" y="54" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a2218"
                    >Non-repeatable read (P2)</text
                >
                <text x="224" y="70" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">same row reads differently</text
                >
                <text x="224" y="82" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">twice = read skew</text>
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="416" y="36" width="190" height="58" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect>
                <text x="426" y="54" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a2218"
                    >Phantom (P3)</text
                >
                <text x="426" y="70" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">a new row changes the</text>
                <text x="426" y="82" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">result of a search</text>
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect
                    x="114"
                    y="108"
                    width="190"
                    height="58"
                    rx="8"
                    fill="#f1eee2"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="124" y="126" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                    >Lost update (P4)</text
                >
                <text x="124" y="142" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">two read-modify-writes</text>
                <text x="124" y="154" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >clobber each other (same row)</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect
                    x="316"
                    y="108"
                    width="190"
                    height="58"
                    rx="8"
                    fill="#f1eee2"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="326" y="126" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                    >Write skew</text
                >
                <text x="326" y="142" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">disjoint writes jointly</text>
                <text x="326" y="154" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">break an invariant</text>
            </g>
            <rect x="60" y="186" width="500" height="48" rx="9" fill="#1c1b18"></rect>
            <text
                x="310"
                y="206"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#f3efe3">Dirty WRITE (P0) is forbidden by EVERY real level —</text
            >
            <text x="310" y="223" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#e8b3a6"
                >allowing it would make atomic rollback impossible.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Berenson et al. (1995) number these P0–P4.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2b">2</a></sup> Adya (1999)
        later recast them as forbidden <em>cycles</em> in a transaction dependency graph — the modern
        lens.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
